 {"id":"bd-mblr.2.3.1","title":"Deterministic fault profile suite","description":"Define deterministic fault profiles (I/O errors, torn writes, partial sync, sidecar corruption) and bind them to invariant checks. Output: fault profile library reused by no-mock and E2E suites.","design":"Implement profiles as composable primitives (pre-write fail, mid-commit fail, replay corruption) to avoid one-off harness hacks.","acceptance_criteria":"- Fault profile catalog defines trigger point, fault shape, expected error/recovery behavior, and invariant checks.
- Profiles are deterministic and seed-addressable for replay.
- Profiles cover I/O failure, torn-write simulation, and corruption-adjacent recovery cases.","notes":"Ensure profile naming maps cleanly to scenario IDs and artifact folder conventions. Fault-profile implementation can proceed before final logging-schema migration, with diagnostics quality validated downstream.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:53.318207015Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:43:36.463220449Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:32.857142673Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:53.318207015Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.2.3.2","title":"Failure replay and minimization harness","description":"Provide replay/minimization tooling for failing fault scenarios so flakes and edge failures become actionable. Output: replay recipe and minimized failing case artifacts.","design":"Use iterative reduction over workload steps while continuously validating invariant breakage to avoid false minimization.","acceptance_criteria":"- Replay tooling can rerun a failing scenario from captured seed/profile/artifact bundle with deterministic output.
- Minimization reduces failing case complexity while preserving invariant violation.
- Output package includes minimized repro recipe and before/after evidence.","notes":"Critical for making rare reliability failures actionable instead of flaky noise.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:53.582745465Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:04:43.883864090Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:53.582745465Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:33.104941565Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:02:49.791561723Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.2.4","title":"Extension Integration on Real Storage Paths","description":"For JSON/FTS/RTREE/session/ext-misc features, add integration tests that execute against real file-backed storage and recovery paths (not only in-memory execution), including reopen and integrity checks.","design":"Treat extension paths as first-class product behavior: tests must validate storage durability and recovery semantics, not just API-level happy paths.","acceptance_criteria":"JSON/FTS/RTREE/session/ext-misc each have file-backed integration tests covering reopen, checkpoint/recovery, and integrity assertions; failures include reproducible fixtures and artifact links.","notes":"Do not accept extension coverage that only passes in-memory pathways when file-backed semantics differ. Structured-log schema conformance is enforced at shared logging gates after scenario implementation.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:03.407710482Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:43:36.526269331Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.4","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:09.735055149Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.4","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:03.407710482Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
